 Medien sowie Lerninfrastrukturen werden vorgestellt. Das Buch bietet zahlreiche Modelle und Praxisbeispiele mit internationalem Bezug (Großbritannien und USA).  aThis book describes the transformation of university and college libraries into teaching libraries which offer space and services for academic learning and promote information literacy in particular. It discusses changes in young people's information behaviour, handling the growing amount of digital information, important skills for searching, selecting, assessing and processing information and media, and learning infrastructures. The book presents a large number of models and practical examples, citing international projects (from the UK and the USA).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aInformationskompetenz. 4aTeaching Library. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Library & Information Science / General.2bisacsh  aInformation Literacy.  aTeaching Library.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Library Information Science 2000 - 2014z9783110636246oZDB-23-GLI08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2012z9783110288995oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LIBRARY AND  INFORMATION SCIENCE  2012z9783110288933oZDB-23-DGB0 cprintz978311027295640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311027301440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110273014423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110273014/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LB  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGBb2012  aZDB-23-DGGb2012  aZDB-23-GLIc2000d2014